\n|}\n\n==1940s==\n{{The Beatles timeline table start}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1940 |m=06 |d=23 |type=L |text=[[Stuart Sutcliffe]] is born in [[Edinburgh]], Scotland.<ref name=\"hill2007p10\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1940 |m=07 |d=07 |type=L |text=Richard Starkey, later known as [[Ringo Starr]], is born at 9 Madryn Street, Dingle, Liverpool.}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1940 |m=10 |d=09 |type=L |text=[[John Lennon]] is born in the Oxford Street Maternity Hospital, Liverpool.<ref name=\"hill2007p10\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline rule}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1941 |m=09 |d=24 |type=L |text=[[Linda McCartney|Linda Eastman]] (later McCartney) is born in New York City. |loc=US}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1941 |m=11 |d=24 |type=L |text=[[Pete Best]] is born in [[Chennai|Madras]], India.<ref name=\"hill2007p10\"/> |loc=India}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline rule}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1942 |m=06 |d=18 |type=L |text=[[Paul McCartney]] is born in the Walton Hospital, Liverpool.<ref name=\"hill2007p10\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline rule}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1943 |m=02 |d=25 |type=L |text=[[George Harrison]] is born at 12 Arnold Grove, Wavertree, Liverpool.<ref name=\"hill2007p10\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline rule}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1944 |m=03 |d=17 |type=L |text=[[Pattie Boyd]] (later Harrison) is born in [[Taunton]], [[Somerset]].}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline rule}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1946 |m=04 |d=05 |type=L |text=[[Jane Asher]] is born in north-west London.}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1946 |m=08 |d=04 |type=L |text=[[Maureen Cox]] (later Starkey) is born in Liverpool.}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline rule}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1947 |m=04 |d=05 |type=L |text=[[Barbara Bach]] (later Starkey) is born in New York City.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://imaginepeace.com/news/archives/8758 |title=Stella McCartney receives a GLAMOUR Women of the Year award from Yoko, Olivia & Barbara |accessdate=11 November 2009}}</ref> |loc=US}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline rule}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1948 |m=05 |d=18 |type=L |text=[[Olivia Trinidad Arias]] (later Harrison) is born in Los Angeles, California. |loc=US}}\n|}\n\n==1950s==\n{{The Beatles timeline table start}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1956 |m=10 |d=31 |type=L |text=McCartney's mother, [[Jim and Mary McCartney|Mary]], dies of [[breast cancer]].<ref name=\"Spitz2005\">{{harvnb|Spitz|2005|p=89}}</ref>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline rule}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1957 |m=03 |d=  |type=B |text=Lennon forms a [[skiffle]] group called the Black Jacks with [[Pete Shotton]]. The band is later renamed [[the Quarrymen]].<ref name=\"hill2007p11\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1957 |m=06 |d=09 |type=PA |text=The Quarrymen audition for [[Carroll Levis]]'s ''TV Star Search'' at the Empire Theatre, Liverpool, but do not qualify.<ref name=\"hill2007p10\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1957 |m=07 |d=06 |type=PC |text=The Quarrymen play at the St Peter's Church garden f\u00eate in Liverpool. McCartney and Lennon meet for the first time.<ref name=\"hill2007p11\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1957 |m=07 |d=20 |type=B |text=McCartney is invited to join the Quarrymen.<ref name=\"hill2007p11\">{{harvnb|Hill|2007|p=11}}</ref>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1957 |m=08 |d=07 |type=PC |text=The Quarrymen perform at [[The Cavern Club]] for the first time.<ref name=\"hill2007p11\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1957 |m=10 |d=18 |type=PC |text=McCartney's first performance with the Quarrymen at the New Clubmoor Hall, Liverpool.<ref name=\"hill2007p11\"/>| McCartney plays lead guitar for the Quarrymen, but gets the solo wrong and is demoted to rhythm guitar.<ref name=\"hill2007p11\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline rule}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1958 |m=02 |d=06 |type=B |text=Harrison meets the Quarrymen, and is invited to join despite being younger than the others.<ref name=\"hill2007p11\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1958 |m=07 |d=09 |type=S |text=The Quarrymen pay 17 pounds and 6 pence to record two songs at a local recording studio in Liverpool, namely \"[[That'll Be the Day]]\" by [[Buddy Holly]] and \"[[In Spite of All the Danger]]\" by Harrison and McCartney.<ref name=\"hill2007p11\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1958 |m=07 |d=15 |type=L |text=Lennon's mother, [[Julia Lennon]], is run over and killed by a speeding car.<ref name=\"hill2007p11\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline rule}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1959 |m=03 |d=25 |type=B |text=Ritchie Starkey is hired as the drummer for \"Al Caldwell and his Raving Texans\" after being spotted on the \"6.5 Special\" talent show. Band members adopt western-sounding stage names, and Starkey becomes [[Ringo Starr]]. The band will shortly change its name to [[Rory Storm and the Hurricanes]].<ref name=\"harryndp2-3\">{{harvnb|Harry|pp=2\u20133}}</ref>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1959 |m=08 |d=29 |type=PC |text=The Quarrymen play at the opening night of the Casbah Club, owned by Best's mother, Mona. The band consists of Lennon, McCartney, Harrison, and Ken Brown, with no drummer.<ref name=\"hill2007p11\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1959 |m=10 |d=10 |type=B |text=Ken Brown leaves the Quarrymen.<ref name=\"hill2007p11\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1959 |m=11 |d=15 |type=PA |text=As Johnny and the Moondogs, Lennon, McCartney and Harrison reach the final audition stage of Carroll Levis's ''TV Star Search'' at the Empire Theatre, Liverpool. Rory Storm and the Hurricanes with Starr finish 2nd out of 150 acts.<ref name=\"hill2007p11\"/><ref name=\"harryndp2-3\"/>}}\n|}\n\n==1960==\n{{The Beatles timeline table start}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1960 |m=05 |d=05 | type=B |text=The Quarrymen change their name to the Silver Beetles<ref name=\"hill2007p12\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1960 |m=05 |d=10 |type=PC |text=The Silver Beetles audition for [[Larry Parnes]] to support [[Billy Fury]] on his next tour. They are unsuccessful, but are offered the chance to support [[Johnny Gentle]] on a tour of Scotland<ref name=\"hill2007p12\">{{harvnb|Hill|2007|p=12}}</ref>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1960 |m=05 |d=14 |type=PC |text=The Silver Beetles play the Lathom Hall, Liverpool<ref name=\"hill2007p12\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1960 |m=05 |d=20 |type=B |text=Sutcliffe plays bass, and Tommy Moore plays drums. The Silver Beetles adopt aliases for the duration of the tour; Lennon becomes ''Long John'', McCartney becomes ''Paul Ramon'', Sutcliffe becomes ''Stuart de Sta\u00ebl'', and Harrison becomes ''Carl Harrison''<ref name=\"hill2007p12\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1960 |m=05 |d=20 |type=PC |text=Johnny Gentle's tour, with the Silver Beetles as his backing band, begins at the Town Hall in [[Alloa]], Scotland.<ref name=\"hill2007p12\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1960 |m=05 |d=21 |type=PC |text=The tour continues at the Rescue Hall in Aberdeen<ref name=\"hill2007p12\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1960 |m=05 |d=21 |type=PC |text=The tour continues to the Northern Meeting Ballroom in [[Inverness]]<ref name=\"hill2007p12\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1960 |m=05 |d=23 |type=PC |text=The next date is the Dalrymple Hall in Fraserburgh, [[Aberdeen]]<ref name=\"hill2007p12\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1960 |m=05 |d=25 |type=PC |text=The tour continues to St Thomas's Hall, [[Banff, Aberdeenshire|Banff]]shire<ref name=\"hill2007p12\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1960 |m=05 |d=26 |type=PC |text=The next tour date is the Town Hall in [[Forres]]<ref name=\"hill2007p12\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1960 |m=05 |d=27 |type=PC |text=The tour continues at the Regal Ballroom, [[Nairn]]<ref name=\"hill2007p12\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1960 |m=05 |d=30 