=The Beatles sign a 1-year contract with Kaempfert<ref name=\"hill2007p14\"/> |loc=GER}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1961 |m=07 |d=01 |type=PC |text=The Beatles' final performance at the Top Ten Club<ref name=\"hill2007p14\"/> |loc=GER}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1961 |m=07 |d=03 |type=O |text=The Beatles return to Liverpool<ref name=\"hill2007p14\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1961 |m=07 |d=06 |type=O |text=The first edition of ''[[Mersey Beat (magazine)|Mersey Beat]]'' is published, and includes an essay by Lennon about the Beatles<ref name=\"hill2007p14\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1961 |m=07 |d=07 |type=L |text=Starr's 21st birthday<ref name=\"hill2007p14\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1961 |m=07 |d=13 |type=PC |text=The Beatles' first performance back in England, at St John's Hall, Tuebrook, Liverpool<ref name=\"hill2007p14\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1961 |m=07 |d=14 |type=PC |text=The Beatles make another appearance at the Cavern Club, to play both the lunchtime and evening slots. The band plays many local gigs\u2014predominately at the Cavern\u2014in the following months<ref name=\"hill2007p14\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1961 |m=07 |d=20 |type=O |text=The Beatles make the front page of ''Mersey Beat'' with a story about their contract with Kaempfert<ref name=\"hill2007p14\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1961 |m=07 |d=27 |type=PC |text=The Beatles are supported at the Cavern Club by Priscilla White, who would later become [[Cilla Black]]<ref name=\"hill2007p14\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline rule}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1961 |m=08 |d=31 |type=O |text=Local DJ [[Bob Wooler]] writes an article on the Beatles for ''Mersey Beat''<ref name=\"hill2007p15\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline rule}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1961 |m=10 |d=09 |type=L |text=Lennon's 21st birthday. He and McCartney celebrate by buying [[bowler hat]]s and [[hitchhiking]] to Paris<ref name=