line rule}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1961 |m=12 |d=01 |type=O |text=The Beatles and Epstein travel to London to meet Colin Borland and Beecher Stevens from [[Decca Records]] in the hope of negotiating a recording contract<ref name=\"hill2007p15\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1961 |m=12 |d=03 |type=O |text=The Beatles and Bob Wooler meet Epstein at his NEMS store<ref name=\"hill2007p15\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1961 |m=12 |d=04 |type=O |text=Deutsche Grammophone representatives meet Epstein in Liverpool to discuss the possibility of releasing \"My Bonnie\" in the UK<ref name=\"hill2007p15\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1961 |m=12 |d=06 |type=O |text=The Beatles meet Epstein at his shop again<ref name=\"hill2007p15\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1961 |m=12 |d=08 |type=O |text=Epstein contacts Ron White of [[EMI]] in the hope of getting the Beatles a record contract<ref name=\"hill2007p15\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1961 |m=12 |d=10 |type=O |text=The Beatles and Epstein meet again, this time at the Casbah Coffee Club<ref name=\"hill2007p15\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1961 |m=12 |d=13 |type=PC |text=Dick Rowe, head of [[Artists and repertoire|A&R]] at Decca, sends Mike Smith to watch the Beatles at the Cavern Club. Smith recommends that Decca set up an audition for the group<ref name=\"hill2007p15\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1961 |m=12 |d=18 |type=O |text=Ron White writes to Epstein to inform him that EMI have rejected the Beatles<ref name=\"hill2007p15\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1961 |m=12 |d=26 |type=PC |text=The Beatles, wrongly billed as the \"Beetles\", play at the \"Big Beat Ball\" at the Tower Ballroom in [[New Brighton, Merseyside]]<ref name=\"hill2007p15\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1961 |m=12 |d=31 |type=O |text=The Beatles travel to London for an audition with Decca the next day<ref name=\"hill2007p15\"/>}}\n|}\n\n==1962==\n{{The Beatles tim