31 |type=L |text=McCartney's mother, [[Jim and Mary McCartney|Mary]], dies of [[breast cancer]].<ref name=\"Spitz2005\">{{harvnb|Spitz|2005|p=89}}</ref>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline rule}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1957 |m=03 |d=  |type=B |text=Lennon forms a [[skiffle]] group called the Black Jacks with [[Pete Shotton]]. The band is later renamed [[the Quarrymen]].<ref name=\"hill2007p11\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1957 |m=06 |d=09 |type=PA |text=The Quarrymen audition for [[Carroll Levis]]'s ''TV Star Search'' at the Empire Theatre, Liverpool, but do not qualify.<ref name=\"hill2007p10\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1957 |m=07 |d=06 |type=PC |text=The Quarrymen play at the St Peter's Church garden f\u00eate in Liverpool. McCartney and Lennon meet for the first time.<ref name=\"hill2007p11\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1957 |m=07 |d=20 |type=B |text=McCartney is invited to join the Quarrymen.<ref name=\"hill2007p11\">{{harvnb|Hill|2007|p=11}}</ref>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1957 |m=08 |d=07 |type=PC |text=The Quarrymen perform at [[The Cavern Club]] for the first time.<ref name=\"hill2007p11\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1957 |m=10 |d=18 |type=PC |text=McCartney's first performance with the Quarrymen at the New Clubmoor Hall, Liverpool.<ref name=\"hill2007p11\"/>| McCartney plays lead guitar for the Quarrymen, but gets the solo wrong and is demoted to rhythm guitar.<ref name=\"hill2007p11\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline rule}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1958 |m=02 |d=06 |type=B |text=Harrison meets the Quarrymen, and is invited to join despite being younger than the others.<ref name=\"hill2007p11\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1958 |m=07 |d=09 |type=S |text=The Quarrymen pay 17 pounds and 6 pence to record two songs at a local recording studio in Liverpool, namely \"[[That'll Be the Day]]\" by [[Buddy Holly]] and \"[[In Spite of All the Danger]]\" by Harrison and McCartney.<ref name=\