s.com|accessdate=26 January 2017}}</ref>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1961 |m=10 |d=17 |type=PC |text=The Beatles' first fan club performance, at the David Lewis Club in Liverpool<ref name=\"hill2007p15\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1961 |m=10 |d=23 |type=RS |text=The single \"[[My Bonnie]]\" / \"[[When the Saints Go Marching In|The Saints]]\" released in Germany<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.beatlesbible.com/discography/germany/2/|title=Beatles discography: Germany|author=Joe Goodden|work=The Beatles Bible|accessdate=11 June 2018}}</ref>|loc=GER}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1961 |m=10 |d=28 |type=O |text=A customer called Raymond Jones enquires about the Beatles' \"[[My Bonnie]]\" single at Epstein's NEMS store, despite the record only being released in Germany. Epstein promises to find it. Alistair Taylor (Epstein's assistant) later erroneously declared that he used Jones' name to order copies of the record himself<ref name=\"hill2007p15\"/><ref name=\"Spitz2005p252\">{{harvnb|Spitz|2005|p=252}}</ref>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1961 |m=10 |d=30 |type=O |text=Two more girls enquire about the record<ref name=\"hill2007p15\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline rule}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1961 |m=11 |d=08 |type=O |text=Epstein books a ticket to see the Beatles at the Cavern Club, citing an \"important visit\"<ref name=\"hill2007p15\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1961 |m=11 |d=09 |type=PC |text=Epstein and his assistant [[Alistair Taylor]] watch the Beatles perform a lunchtime show at the Cavern Club<ref name=\"hill2007p15\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline rule}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1961 |m=12 |d=01 |type=O |text=The Beatles and Epstein travel to London to meet Colin Borland and Beecher Stevens from [[Decca Records]] in the hope of negotiating a recording contract<ref name=\"hill2007p15\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1961 |m=12 |d=03 |type=O |text=The Beatles and Bob Wooler meet Epstein at h