les1998p72\">{{harvnb|Miles|1998|p=72}}</ref>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1962 |m=09 |d=10 |type=O |text=Lennon and Harrison buy new guitars from Rushworth and Dreaper's in Liverpool<ref name=\"hill2007p20\">{{harvnb|Hill|2007|p=20}}</ref>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1962 |m=09 |d=11 |type=S |text=The Beatles record \"[[P.S. I Love You (The Beatles song)|P.S. I Love You]]\" and \"Love Me Do\".<ref name=\"hill2007p20\"/> This recording of the latter will be included on the album. \"[[Please Please Me (song)|Please Please Me]]\" is also performed, in a slower tempo, but not recorded; Martin suggests it be reworked.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.beatlesebooks.com/please-please-me|title=PLEASE PLEASE ME|publisher=beatlesebooks.com|accessdate=16 June 2018}}</ref>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1962 |m=09 |d=11 |type=B |text=Session drummer [[Andy White (drummer)|Andy White]] plays drums while Starr plays percussion accompaniments. This is the only occasion on which a session drummer is used on Beatles recordings.<ref name=\"hill2007p20\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline rule}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1962 |m=10 |d=01 |type=O |text=The Beatles sign a new contract with Epstein<ref name=\"hill2007p20\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1962 |m=10 |d=05 |type=RS |text=\"[[Love Me Do]]\" / \"[[P.S. I Love You (The Beatles song)|P.S. I Love You]]\" released,<ref name=\"lewisohn1p200-201\"/> and played on [[Radio Luxembourg (English)|Radio Luxembourg]]<ref name=\"hill2007p20\"/>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=1962 |m=10 |d=06 |type=O |text=The Beatles sign copies of their new single at Dawson's Music Shop in [[Widnes]], [[Cheshire]]\u2014the first of many such public appearances<ref name=\"hill2007p20\"/><ref name=\"beatlesstory-widnes\">{{cite news |publisher=The Beatles Story |url=http://www.beatlesstory.com/news.asp?key=19&nkey=400 |title=Widnes-owned Beatles single sells for thousands!}}</ref>}}\n\n{{The Beatles timeline event |y=