22/doc-iihnzahk5804410.shtml|title=\u6d77\u5357\u786e\u8bca4\u4f8b\u65b0\u578b\u51a0\u72b6\u75c5\u6bd2\u611f\u67d3\u7684\u80ba\u708e|last=\u56fd\u9645\u5728\u7ebf|date=2020-01-22|website=tech.sina.com.cn|access-date=2020-01-22}}</ref> Hunan reported three additional laboratory-confirmed cases.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u6e56\u5357\u7701\u65b0\u589e3\u4f8b\u65b0\u578b\u51a0\u72b6\u75c5\u6bd2\u611f\u67d3\u7684\u80ba\u708e\u786e\u8bca\u75c5\u4f8b - \u6e56\u5357\u7701\u536b\u751f\u5065\u5eb7\u59d4\u5458\u4f1a |url=http://wjw.hunan.gov.cn/wjw/xxgk/gzdt/zyxw_1/202001/t20200122_11163560.html |website=wjw.hunan.gov.cn |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229115153/http://wjw.hunan.gov.cn/wjw/xxgk/gzdt/zyxw_1/202001/t20200122_11163560.html |archivedate=29 February 2020 |language=zh |date=22 January 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> [[Guangxi]] reported two laboratory-confirmed cases.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wsjkw.gxzf.gov.cn/gzdt/bt/2020/0122/67925.html|title=\u5e7f\u897f\u786e\u8bca2\u4f8b\u65b0\u578b\u51a0\u72b6\u75c5\u6bd2\u611f\u67d3\u7684\u80ba\u708e\u75c5\u4f8b|last=|first=|date=|website=|access-date=}}</ref> In all, the total number of laboratory-confirmed cases in China increased to 571 and the death toll to 17.\n\nInternationally, two more laboratory-confirmed cases were reported in Thailand, raising the total number of laboratory-confirmed cases in Thailand to four.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asia/wuhan-virus-china-two-more-cases-found-thailand-12301606|title=Wuhan virus: 2 more cases confirmed in Thailand|website=CNA|access-date=2020-01-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200122134115/https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asia/wuhan-virus-china-two-more-cases-found-thailand-12301606|archive-date=22 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nNew data showed indications of the current rapid spread of the disease and an increase in the rate of transmission.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Bostock |first1=Bill |title=A terrifying graph shows how fast the Wuhan virus has spread so far and how close it is to becoming a pandemic |url=https://www.yahoo.com/news/terrifying-graph-shows-fast-wuhan-103230506.html |website=[[Yahoo! News]] |publisher=[[Business Insider]] |language=en |date=22 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Thompson |first1=Alexandra |title=China's coronavirus could have same death rate as Spanish flu outbreak in the UK |url=https://www.yahoo.com/lifestyle/chinas-coronavirus-has-the-same-death-rate-as-the-spanish-flu-pandemic-that-killed-50-m-people-151608803.html |website=[[Yahoo!]] |date=20 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nOfficials announced a quarantine of the greater Wuhan, China area to commence on 23 January 2020 at 10:00 a.m. No traffic would be allowed in or out of the city.<ref>{{cite tweet |user=ChinaDaily |number=1220052882596286465 |date=22 January 2020 |title=Public transportation such as bus, subway, ferry and long-distance bus in Wuhan will be temporarily closed... |access-date=8 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200201183636/https://twitter.com/ChinaDaily/status/1220052882596286465 |archive-date=1 February 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nZhou Xianwang, the mayor of Wuhan, admitted that his team had not released information about the virus in a \"timely\" manner, resulting in over 5 million people traveled out of the city before Wuhan was placed in quarantine. Zhou indicated that Wuhan needed authorization from above before they could make any announcement regarding the virus.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Pai |first1=Akshay |title=Wuhan mayor admits 'withholding' information about outbreak, scientists fear 100,000 have already been infected |url=https://meaww.com/wuhan-coronavirus-mayor-admits-withholding-information-about-deadly-outbreak-offers-to-resign |website=meaww.com |accessdate=8 April 2020 |language=en |date=27 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Zheng |first1=Sarah |title=Wuhan mayor under pressure to resign over response to virus outbreak |url=https://www.scmp.com/news/china/politics/article/3047230/wuhan-mayor-under-pressure-resign-over-response-coronavirus |website=South China Morning Post |accessdate=8 April 2020 |language=en |date=23 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nUS Embassy in China raised the Health Alert to level 2 (Practice Enhanced Precautions).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://china.usembassy-china.org.cn/health-alert-update-novel-coronavirus-in-china-3/ |title=Health Alert Update \u2013 Novel Coronavirus in China-Level 2 &#124; U.S. Embassy & Consulates in China |publisher=China.usembassy-china.org.cn |date=2020-01-22 |accessdate=2020-04-10}}</ref>. President Trump during an interview at Economic Forum in Switzerland that \"It\u2019s one person coming in from China, and we have it under control. It\u2019s\u2014going to be just fine.\"<ref name=\":1\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2020/01/22/davos-2020-cnbcs-full-interview-with-president-trump.html|title=Full interview: President Trump discusses trade, impeachment, Boeing and Elon Musk with CNBC in Davos|last=Calia|first=Mike|date=2020-01-22|website=CNBC|language=en|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n\n===23 January===\n'''WHO''' Situation Report 3:<ref>{{Citation|url=https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200123-sitrep-3-2019-ncov.pdf?sfvrsn=d6d23643_8|title=Novel Coronavirus (2019-nCoV) Situation Report - 3 23 January 2020|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206035857/https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200123-sitrep-3-2019-ncov.pdf?sfvrsn=d6d23643_8|archive-date=6 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n[[Jiangsu]] reported its first laboratory-confirmed case.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wjw.jiangsu.gov.cn/art/2020/1/23/art_7290_8955651.html|title=\u6c5f\u82cf\u7701\u536b\u751f\u5065\u5eb7\u59d4\u5458\u4f1a \u8981\u95fb\u52a8\u6001 \u56fd\u5bb6\u536b\u751f\u5065\u5eb7\u59d4\u786e\u8ba4\u82cf\u5dde\u4e00\u4f8b\u65b0\u578b\u51a0\u72b6\u75c5\u6bd2\u611f\u67d3\u7684\u80ba\u708e\u786e\u8bca\u75c5\u4f8b|website=wjw.jiangsu.gov.cn|access-date=2020-01-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200123161923/http://wjw.jiangsu.gov.cn/art/2020/1/23/art_7290_8955651.html|archive-date=2020-01-23|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Heilongjiang]] reported its first two laboratory-confirmed cases.<ref>{{cite web |title=2020\u5e741\u670823\u65e5\u65b0\u578b\u51a0\u72b6\u75c5\u6bd2\u611f\u67d3\u7684\u80ba\u708e\u75ab\u60c5\u60c5\u51b5_\u90e8\u95e8\u653f\u52a1_\u4e2d\u56fd\u653f\u5e9c\u7f51 |url=http://www.gov.cn/xinwen/2020-01/23/content_5471771.htm |website=www.gov.cn |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200126012531/http://www.gov.cn/xinwen/2020-01/23/content_5471771.htm |archivedate=26 January 2020 |language=zh |date=23 January 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://wsjkw.gxzf.gov.cn/gzdt/bt/2020/0123/67932.html|title=\u5e7f\u897f\u65b0\u589e3\u4f8b\u65b0\u578b\u51a0\u72b6\u75c5\u6bd2\u611f\u67d3\u7684\u80ba\u708e\u786e\u8bca\u75c5\u4f8b|date=23 January 2020|website=wsjkw.gxzf.gov.cn}}</ref> Shanghai reported an additional seven laboratory-confirmed cases.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.sina.com.cn/c/2020-01-23/doc-iihnzhha4251036.shtml|title=\u4e0a\u6d77\u65b0\u589e7\u4f8b\u65b0\u578b\u51a0\u72b6\u75c5\u6bd2\u611f\u67d3\u7684\u80ba\u708e\u786e\u8bca\u75c5\u4f8b|last=\u5065\u5eb7\u4e0a\u6d7712320|date=23 January 2020|website=news.sina.com.cn|access-date=23 January 2020}}</ref> [[Xinjiang]] reported two laboratory-confirmed cases.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bjnews.com.cn/news/2020/01/23/678507.html|title=\u65b0\u7586\u9996\u6b21\u786e\u8bca2\u4f8b\u8f93\u5165\u6027\u65b0\u578b\u51a0\u72b6\u75c5\u6bd2\u611f\u67d3\u7684\u80ba\u708e\u75c5\u4f8b|last=www.bjnews.com.cn|website=www.bjnews.com.cn|access-date=24 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200124063007/http://www.bjnews.com.cn/news/2020/01/23/678507.html|archive-date=2020-01-24|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Shaanxi]] reported three laboratory-confirmed cases.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bjnews.com.cn/news/2020/01/23/678506.html|title=\u9655\u897f\u786e\u8bca3\u4f8b\u65b0\u578b\u80ba\u708e\u75c5\u4f8b|last=www.bjnews.com.cn|website=www.bjnews.com.cn|access-date=2020-01-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200124035900/http://www.bjnews.com.cn/news/2020/01/23/678506.html|archive-date=2020-01-24|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Gansu]] reported two laboratory-confirmed cases.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wsjk.gansu.gov.cn/single/10910/82997.html|title=\u7518\u8083\u7701\u786e\u8ba42\u4f8b\u65b0\u578b\u51a0\u72b6\u75c5\u6bd2\u611f\u67d3\u7684\u80ba\u708e\u786e\u8bca\u75c5\u4f8b|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200128195957/http://wsjk.gansu.gov.cn/single/10910/82997.html|archive-date=28 January 2020|access-date=}}</ref> Macau also reported its second laboratory-confirmed case, another 66-year-old man from Wuhan.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.scmp.com/news/china/article/3047337/macau-confirms-second-patient-infected-chinese-coronavirus|title=Macau confirms second patient infected with Wuhan virus|date=2020-01-23|website=South China Morning Post|access-date=2020-01-23}}</ref> In all, the total number of laboratory-confirmed cases in mainland China increased to 628 while the death toll remained at 17.\n\n[[Singapore]] reported its first laboratory-confirmed case, a 66-year-old man from China.<ref name=\"Update23Jan\">{{cite web|last1=Goh|first1=Timothy|last2=Toh|first2=Ting Wei|title=Singapore confirms first case of Wuhan virus|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/health/singapore-confirms-first-case-of-wuhan-virus|website=The Straits Times|accessdate=23 January 2020|date=23 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200124014101/https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/health/singapore-confirms-first-case-of-wuhan-virus|archive-date=24 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Vietnam]] confirmed its first two laboratory-confirmed cases, a 65 or 66-year-old father and 27 or 28-year-old son from China.<ref name=\"Vietnam23Jan2020\">{{cite news|url=https://e.vnexpress.net/news/news/vietnam-confirms-first-acute-pneumonia-cases-from-wuhan-virus-4046310.html|title=Vietnam confirms first acute pneumonia cases from Wuhan virus|date=23 January 2020}}</ref><ref name=Phan28Jan2020>{{Cite journal|doi= 10.1056/NEJMc2001272|pmid= 31991079|title= Importation and Human-to-Human Transmission of a Novel Coronavirus in Vietnam|year = 2020|last1 = Phan|first1 = Lan T.|last2 = Nguyen|first2 = Thuong V.|last3 = Luong|first3 = Quang C.|last4 = Nguyen|first4 = Thinh V.|last5 = Nguyen|first5 = Hieu T.|last6 = Le|first6 = Hung Q.|last7 = Nguyen|first7 = Thuc T.|last8 = Cao|first8 = Thang M.|last9 = Pham|first9 = Quang D.|journal = New England Journal of Medicine|volume = 382|issue = 9|pages = 872\u2013874|pmc= 7121428}}</ref>\n\nA scientific preprint from the Wuhan institute of Virology is posted on [[Biorxiv]] (later published in ''[[Nature (journal)|Nature]]''<ref>{{Cite journal|title=A pneumonia outbreak associated with a new coronavirus of probable bat origin|first1=Peng|last1=Zhou|first2=Xing-Lou|last2=Yang|first3=Xian-Guang|last3=Wang|first4=Ben|last4=Hu|first5=Lei|last5=Zhang|first6=Wei|last6=Zhang|first7=Hao-Rui|last7=Si|first8=Yan|last8=Zhu|first9=Bei|last9=Li|first10=Chao-Lin|last10=Huang|first11=Hui-Dong|last11=Chen|first12=Jing|last12=Chen|first13=Yun|last13=Luo|first14=Hua|last14=Guo|first15=Ren-Di|last15=Jiang|first16=Mei-Qin|last16=Liu|first17=Ying|last17=Chen|first18=Xu-Rui|last18=Shen|first19=Xi|last19=Wang|first20=Xiao-Shuang|last20=Zheng|first21=Kai|last21=Zhao|first22=Quan-Jiao|last22=Chen|first23=Fei|last23=Deng|first24=Lin-Lin|last24=Liu|first25=Bing|last25=Yan|first26=Fa-Xian|last26=Zhan|first27=Yan-Yi|last27=Wang|first28=Geng-Fu|last28=Xiao|first29=Zheng-Li|last29=Shi|date=1 March 2020|journal=Nature|volume=579|issue=7798|pages=270\u2013273|doi=10.1038/s41586-020-2012-7|pmid=32015507|pmc=7095418}}</ref>) announcing that a bat virus with 96% similarity had been sequenced in a Yunnan cave in 2013, whose sequence is posted the next day on public databases. It is  confirmed by comparing infectivity of cells expressing or not expressing [[ACE2]] that the novel coronavirus uses this same entry receptor as [[SARS-CoV]].<ref>{{Citation|title=Discovery of a novel coronavirus associated with the recent pneumonia outbreak in humans and its potential bat origin\n|year=2020|doi=10.1101/2020.01.22.914952|url=https://www.biorxiv.org/content/10.1101/2020.01.22.914952v2|last1=Zhou|first1=Peng|last2=Yang|first2=Xing-Lou|last3=Wang|first3=Xian-Guang|last4=Hu|first4=Ben|last5=Zhang|first5=Lei|last6=Zhang|first6=Wei|last7=Si|first7=Hao-Rui|last8=Zhu|first8=Yan|last9=Li|first9=Bei|last10=Huang|first10=Chao-Lin|last11=Chen|first11=Hui-Dong|last12=Chen|first12=Jing|last13=Luo|first13=Yun|last14=Guo|first14=Hua|last15=Jiang|first15=Ren-Di|last16=Liu|first16=Mei-Qin|last17=Chen|first17=Ying|last18=Shen|first18=Xu-Rui|last19=Wang|first19=Xi|last20=Zheng|first20=Xiao-Shuang|last21=Zhao|first21=Kai|last22=Chen|first22=Quan-Jiao|last23=Deng|first23=Fei|last24=Liu|first24=Lin-Lin|last25=Yan|first25=Bing|last26=Zhan|first26=Fa-Xian|last27=Wang|first27=Yan-Yi|last28=Xiao|first28=Geng-Fu|last29=Shi|first29=Zheng-Li|doi-access=free}}</ref>\n\nWuhan [[2020 Wuhan lockdown|suspended all public transportation]] from 10 a.m. onwards, including all bus, metro and ferry lines. Additionally, all outbound trains and flights were halted.<ref name=\":7\">{{cite web|url=https://view.inews.qq.com/w/WXN2020012301001306?uid=&devid=A55D8C74-EEF2-420C-8182-21F1D43348CF&qimei=34ae00a5-9e85-4f82-9afa-3c7ccb6d36d5|title=\u76f4\u51fb\u6b66\u6c49\u5929\u6cb3\u673a\u573a\uff1a\"\u5c01\u57ce\"\u524d\u670996\u67b6\u822a\u73ed\u98de\u5f80\u5168\u56fd|last=|first=|date=|website=|access-date=2020-01-23}}</ref>\n\n===24 January===\nAccording to data published in ''[[The Lancet]]'' medical journal, 13 of the initial 41 cases of the novel coronavirus had no link with the wet market in Wuhan purported to be the origin of the disease.<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Clinical features of patients infected with 2019 novel coronavirus in Wuhan, China|first1=Chaolin|last1=Huang|first2=Yeming|last2=Wang|first3=Xingwang|last3=Li|first4=Lili|last4=Ren|first5=Jianping|last5=Zhao|first6=Yi|last6=Hu|first7=Li|last7=Zhang|first8=Guohui|last8=Fan|first9=Jiuyang|last9=Xu|first10=Xiaoying|last10=Gu|first11=Zhenshun|last11=Cheng|first12=Ting|last12=Yu|first13=Jiaan|last13=Xia|first14=Yuan|last14=Wei|first15=Wenjuan|last15=Wu|first16=Xuelei|last16=Xie|first17=Wen|last17=Yin|first18=Hui|last18=Li|first19=Min|last19=Liu|first20=Yan|last20=Xiao|first21=Hong|last21=Gao|first22=Li|last22=Guo|first23=Jungang|last23=Xie|first24=Guangfa|last24=Wang|first25=Rongmeng|last25=Jiang|first26=Zhancheng|last26=Gao|first27=Qi|last27=Jin|first28=Jianwei|last28=Wang|first29=Bin|last29=Cao|date=9 February 2020|journal=The Lancet|volume=395|issue=10223|pages=497\u2013506|doi=10.1016/s0140-6736(20)30183-5|pmid = 31986264}}</ref>\n\nOne of the earlier studies on person-to-person transmission was published by Hong Kong doctors in [[The Lancet|''The Lancet'']] titled \"A familial cluster of pneumonia associated with the 2019 novel coronavirus indicating person-to-person transmission: a study of a family cluster\". In the \"Evidence before this study\" it declared that \"we searched PubMed on Jan 13, 2020, with no starting date limitations, using the terms \u201cfamily\u201d, \u201cpneumonia\u201d, \u201cWuhan\u201d, \u201ccoronavirus\u201d, and \u201cnovel\u201d for articles in English. Our search did not reveal any reports of novel coronavirus pneumonia in Wuhan before 2020. We only noted family clusters of pneumonia due to the novel severe acute respiratory syndrome (SARS) coronavirus in 2003, and Middle East respiratory syndrome coronavirus in 2012.\"<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Chan|first=Jasper Fuk-Woo|last2=Yuan|first2=Shuofeng|last3=Kok|first3=Kin-Hang|last4=To|first4=Kelvin Kai-Wang|last5=Chu|first5=Hin|last6=Yang|first6=Jin|last7=Xing|first7=Fanfan|last8=Liu|first8=Jieling|last9=Yip|first9=Cyril Chik-Yan|last10=Poon|first10=Rosana Wing-Shan|last11=Tsoi|first11=Hoi-Wah|date=2020-02-15|title=A familial cluster of pneumonia associated with the 2019 novel coronavirus indicating person-to-person transmission: a study of a family cluster|url=https://www.thelancet.com/journals/lancet/article/PIIS0140-6736(20)30154-9/abstract|journal=The Lancet|language=English|volume=395|issue=10223|pages=514\u2013523|doi=10.1016/S0140-6736(20)30154-9|issn=0140-6736|pmid=31986261|doi-access=free}}</ref>\n\n'''WHO''' Situation Report 4:<ref>{{Citation|url=https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200124-sitrep-4-2019-ncov.pdf?sfvrsn=9272d086_8|title=Novel Coronavirus (2019-nCoV) Situation Report - 4 24 January 2020|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206013156/https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200124-sitrep-4-2019-ncov.pdf?sfvrsn=9272d086_8|archive-date=6 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n[[File:\u9999\u6e2f\u786e\u8bca\u4e24\u5b97\u65b0\u578b\u80ba\u708e\u4e2a\u6848 \u673a\u573a\u706b\u8f66\u7ad9\u52a0\u5f3a\u4f53\u6e29\u7b5b\u67e5.webm|thumb|right|'Hong Kong confirms two new cases of pneumonia' - video news report from [[China News Service]], January 24, 2020 (Captions available in English)]]\nShandong reported six additional laboratory-confirmed cases.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wsjkw.shandong.gov.cn/wzxxgk/zwgg/202001/t20200124_2511713.html|title=2020\u5e741\u670824\u65e50\u65f6\u81f312\u65f6\u5c71\u4e1c\u7701\u65b0\u578b\u51a0\u72b6\u75c5\u6bd2\u611f\u67d3\u7684\u80ba\u708e\u75ab\u60c5\u60c5\u51b5|last=|first=|date=|website=|access-date=}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}{{Dead link|date=February 2020|bot=InternetArchiveBot|fix-attempted=yes}}</ref> Hunan reported 15 additional laboratory-confirmed cases.<