arts            = 2\n| Title_1             = Cooler Parasol\n| TranslitTitle_1     = K\u016br\u0101 Parasoru no Maki\n| NativeTitle_1       = \u30af\u30fc\u30e9\u30fc\u30d1\u30e9\u30bd\u30eb\u306e\u5dfb\n| Title_2             = Always Diary\n| TranslitTitle_2     = Itsudemo Nikki no Maki\n| NativeTitle_2       = \u3044\u3064\u3067\u3082\u65e5\u8a18\u306e\u5dfb\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1973|8|19}}\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 21\n| NumParts            = 2\n| Title_1             = The Homework Ghost Came Out\n| TranslitTitle_1     = Shukudai Obake ga Deta no Maki\n| NativeTitle_1       = \u5bbf\u984c\u304a\u3070\u3051\u304c\u51fa\u305f\u306e\u5dfb\n| Title_2             = Weather Box\n| TranslitTitle_2     = Otenki Bokkusu no Maki\n| NativeTitle_2       = \u304a\u5929\u6c17\u30dc\u30c3\u30af\u30b9\u306e\u5dfb\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1973|8|26}}\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 22\n| NumParts            = 2\n| Title_1             = I Have One Vote of Betrayal\n| TranslitTitle_1     = Boku ni Kiyoki Ichi Py\u014d wo no Maki\n| NativeTitle_1       = \u307c\u304f\u306b\u6e05\u304d\u4e00\u7968\u3092\u306e\u5dfb\n| Title_2             = Manga Artist Training\n| TranslitTitle_2     = Manga Ka Shugy\u014d no Maki\n| NativeTitle_2       = \u307e\u3093\u304c\u5bb6\u4fee\u884c\u306e\u5dfb\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1973|9|2}}\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 23\n| NumParts            = 2\n| Title_1             = Nice Girlfriend\n| TranslitTitle_1     = Sutekina G\u0101rufurendo no Maki\n| NativeTitle_1       = \u3059\u3066\u304d\u306a\u30ac\u30fc\u30eb\u30d5\u30ec\u30f3\u30c9\u306e\u5dfb\n| Title_2             = Flowery Riot\n| TranslitTitle_2     = Gaippai S\u014dd\u014d no Maki\n| NativeTitle_2       = \u82b1\u3044\u3063\u3071\u3044\u9a12\u52d5\u306e\u5dfb\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1973|9|9}}\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 24\n| NumParts            = 2\n| Title_1             = Entirely Crayon\n| TranslitTitle_1     = Sokkuri Kureyon no Maki\n| NativeTitle_1       = \u305d\u3063\u304f\u308a\u30af\u30ec\u30e8\u30f3\u306e\u5dfb\n| Title_2             = Sue's Birthday\n| TranslitTitle_2     = Shizuka no Tanj\u014dbi no Maki\n| NativeTitle_2       = \u9759\u9999\u306e\u8a95\u751f\u65e5\u306e\u5dfb\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1973|9|16}}\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 25\n| NumParts            = 2\n| Title_1             = Becoming a Space Astronaut\n| TranslitTitle_1     = Uch\u016b Hik\u014dshi ni Naritai no Maki\n| NativeTitle_1       = \u5b87\u5b99\u98db\u884c\u58eb\u306b\u306a\u308a\u305f\u3044\u306e\u5dfb\n| Title_2             = Lost and Confused Riot\n| TranslitTitle_2     = Maigo Magomago \u014cs\u014dd\u014d no Maki\n| NativeTitle_2       = \u307e\u3044\u3054\u30de\u30b4\u30de\u30b4\u5927\u9a12\u52d5\u306e\u5dfb\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1973|9|23}}\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 26\n| NumParts            = 2\n| Title_1             = Nendoron Riot\n| TranslitTitle_1     = Nendoron \u014cs\u014dd\u014d no Maki\n| NativeTitle_1       = \u30cd\u30f3\u30c9\u30ed\u30f3\u5927\u9a12\u52d5\u306e\u5dfb\n| Title_2             = Goodbye, Doraemon\n| TranslitTitle_2     = Say\u014dnara Doraemon no Maki\n| NativeTitle_2       = \u3055\u3088\u3046\u306a\u3089\u30c9\u30e9\u3048\u3082\u3093\u306e\u5dfb\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1973|9|30}}\n}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{ann|anime|1317}}\n* [http://kougasetumei.hatenablog.com/entry/ntvdoraemon Doraemon (1973 TV series) Design Works]\n\n{{Doraemon}}\n\n[[Category:Doraemon (anime)]]\n[[Category:1973 anime television series]]\n[[Category:Lost television programs]]\n[[Category:Nippon Television shows]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox television season\n| season_number        = \n| bgcolour             = #40c5eb\n| image                = Doraemon 1973 anime.png\n| image_size           = 250px\n| image_alt            = \n| caption              = Doraemon logo\n| starring             = \n| country              = Japan\n| num_episodes         = 26\n| network              = [[Nippon TV]]\n| first_aired          = '''Pilot''':<br />1972<br />'''Official''':<br />{{Start date|1973|4|1}}\n| last_aired           = {{End date|1973|9|30}}\n| prev_season          = \n| next_season          = [[Doraemon (1979 anime)|1979 anime]]\n| episode_list         = \n}}\n{{More citations needed|date=February 2019}}\n{{nihongo|'''''Doraemon'''''|\u30c9\u30e9\u3048\u3082\u3093|Doraemon}} is the first [[anime]] [[TV series]] based on [[Fujiko Fujio]]'s [[Doraemon|manga of the same name]]. It was produced by Nippon Television Douga (previously known as Japan Broadcast Film, and Tokyo TV Movie). It aired from April 1, 1973 to September 30, 1973. After the anime ended, Doraemon remained exclusively a manga until 1979 when [[Shin-Ei Animation]] produced a more successful [[Doraemon (1979 anime)|second anime adaptation]], which officially ended in 2005; it was in turn replaced by a [[Doraemon (2005 anime)|third anime adaptation]] shortly after which continues to air to recent days.\n\n==Characters==\n{{main|List of Doraemon characters}}\n\n==Voice cast==\n[[File:Doraemon characters (1973).png|thumb|right|Cast of the 1973 version]]\nThe voice cast was determined in cooperation with [[Aoni Production]] and Theatre Echo\n* Doraemon \u2013 [[K\u014dsei Tomita]] (from episode 1A to 13B) and [[Masako Nozawa]] (from Episode 14A to 26B)\n*Nobita Nobi \u2013 [[:ja:\u592a\u7530\u6dd1\u5b50|Yoshiko Ota]]\n*Shizuka Minamoto \u2013 [[:ja:\u6075\u6bd4\u5bff\u307e\u3055\u5b50|Ebisu Masako]]\n*Suneo \u2013 [[Shun Yashiro]]\n*Takeshi (Gian) Gouda \u2013 [[Kaneta Kimotsuki]]\n*Tamako Nobi \u2013 [[Noriko Ohara]]\n*Nobisuke Nobi - [[Ichir\u014d Murakoshi]]\n*Suneo's Mother - [[Kazue Takahashi]]\n*Suneo's Father - from [[Sanji Hase]] to [[:ja:\u52a0\u85e4\u6cbb|Osamu Kat\u014d]]\n*Gian's Father - unknown\n*Sewashi - [[Keiko Yamamoto]]\n*Ganari - from [[:ja:\u52a0\u85e4\u6cbb|Osamu Kat\u014d]] to [[Masashi Amenomori]]\n*Gachako - [[Junko Hori]]\n*Botako - [[Masako Nozawa]]\n*Damako - [[Noriko Tsukase]]\n*Jamako - [[Rihoko Yoshida]]\n\n==Production and Broadcast==\nThe series was broadcast between May 25 to September 30, 1973 on [[Nippon TV|Nippon Television]]. 26 episodes, divided into 52 individual segments were produced. A pilot film was produced in 1972 and shown to test audiences in January 1973. Audience included Doraemon creator [[Fujiko Fujio]]. They initially approved of the show, but when they were shown the progress, they apparently were angered by the fact that they changed Nobita and Doraemon's personalities.{{Citation needed|date=February 2019}} The show was frequently rebroadcast throughout the 1970s. The station, [[Toyama Television]], was the last to air the show, airing from July 3 to July 24, 1981, and briefly again in August of that year. The station aired the show in individual segments. On August 3, the [[Shogakukan|publisher]] of the Doraemon manga requested the station to cease airing the show, to make sure the reputation of the more famous and longer running [[Doraemon (1979 anime)|1979 series]] isn't harmed. The animation crew of the show, [[Nippon TeleMovie Productions]], went bankrupt in 1981. Before they went defunct, they tried covering debt by selling off the masters of the 1973 series, and destroying [[cel]]s and [[storyboards]] in a kerosene fire. In 1995, the Japanese animation studio [[Imagica|IMAGICA]], discovered episodes 18 and 20 through 26 in their archive, as well as segments 5A, 10B and 12B.\n\nIn 2003, the production chief of the show, [[:ja:\u771f\u4f50\u7f8e\u30b8\u30e5\u30f3|Hiroshi Shimozaki]], now going under the name Masumi Jun or \"mcsammy\", came forward with several episodes and [[rush reels]] (raw footage). He later uploaded low quality versions of the intro and credits to his site on a members only and password protected page, however, a few minutes after the upload, he was told that the intro and credits were uploaded to Japanese anonymous board site [[2channel]]. He immediately removed the video files from his site, but it was already too late. Many images of his episodes were uploaded to GeoCities. In the late 1990s, a person came forward with a [[VHS]] recording of the episode \"Crazy Stomach Clock\", dated from 1978. Audio clips were uploaded, but the site they were hosted on was removed. In 2015, a YouTube user discovered a clip playing on a television set in a Japanese pornographic film from the 1970s.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://cartoonresearch.com/index.php/the-strange-case-of-the-1973-doraemon-series |title=The Strange Case of the 1973 \u201cDoraemon\u201d Series |last=Brubaker |first=Charles |date=May 28, 2013 |publisher=Cartoon Research |access-date=November 15, 2016}}</ref>\nIt is what seems like impossible to find info on this version of Doraemon. No episodes exist online, or on home media besides an audio recording of the final episode. The only footage currently available is Jun's uploads of the opening and ending. However, the footage is of very low quality ([[240p]] 193kbit/s video, 128kbit/s audio).\n\n==Episodes==\n{{No plot|section|date=May 2018}}\n{|class=\"wikitable\" width=\"99%\"\n|-style=\"border-bottom:3px solid #CCF\"\n!width=\"7%\"|#\n!Title\n!width=\"15%\"|Original airdate\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 1\n| NumParts            = 2\n| Title_1             = Doraemon Came Out!!\n| TranslitTitle_1     = Deta!! Doraemon no Maki\n| NativeTitle_1       = \u51fa\u305f\uff01\uff01\u30c9\u30e9\u3048\u3082\u3093\u306e\u5dfb\n| Title_2             = The Apology Grasshopper Riot\n| TranslitTitle_2     = Pekopekobatta \u014cs\u014dd\u014d no Maki\n| NativeTitle_2       =