hy|first=Michael A.|date=30 May 2019|url=https://jacobinmag.com/2019/05/bernie-sanders-meidner-plan-worker-ownership|title=Economic Democracy, If We Can Keep It|newspaper=Jacobin|accessdate=20 July 2019|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite news|last=McEvoy|first=John|date=18 May 2019|url=http://axisoflogic.com/artman/publish/Article_84551.shtml|title=Mexico has huge plans to decriminalise all drugs \u2013 and wants the US to do the same|website=Axis of Logic|accessdate=15 January 2020|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite news|last=McSheffrey|first=Elizabeth|date=21 October 2015|url=https://www.nationalobserver.com/2015/10/21/opinion/better-luck-next-time-mr-mulcair|title=Better luck next time, Mr. Mulcair|newspaper=National Observer|accessdate=8 February 2020|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite news|last=Meyer|first=David|date=20 June 2019|url=https://fortune.com/2019/06/20/bernie-sanders-employee-ownership-uk/|title=Bernie Sanders Wants Companies to Give Employees Ownership\u2014a Trend That's Already Growing in the U.K.|newspaper=Fortune|accessdate=20 July 2019|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite news|last=Mitgang|first=Herbert|date=2 August 1989|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1989/08/02/obituaries/michael-harrington-socialist-and-author-is-dead.html|title=Michael Harrington, Socialist and Author, Is Dead|newspaper=The New York Times|accessdate=9 February 2020|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite news|last=Monahan|first=Sean|date=6 March 2015|url=https://www.jacobinmag.com/2015/03/thomas-paine-american-revolution-common-sense/|title=Reading Paine From the Left|newspaper=Jacobin|accessdate=13 February 2020|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Morley|first=James W.|year=1993|title=Driven by Growth: Political Change in the Asia-Pacific Region|location=Armonk, New York|publisher=M. E. Sharpe|isbn=978-0-7656-3344-6|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite news|last=Muldoon|first=James|date=5 January 2019|url=https://www.jacobinmag.com/2019/01/karl-kautsky-german-revolution-democracy-socialism|title=Reclaiming the Best of Karl Kautsky|newspaper=Jacobin|accessdate=20 June 201